node.title: Young man who died following 'altercation' between two groups in Manukau Velodrome carpark named
node.description: "Our thoughts and sympathies are with Mr Tauiti's family."
node.content: ["The young man who died following an \"altercation\" in the Manukau Velodrome carpark on New Year's Day has now been named as 21-year-old Joseph Tauiti.", "Police launched a homicide investigation on Saturday after Tauiti was rushed to Middlemore Hospital at about 6am with \"critical injuries\" and died a short time later.\u00a0", "On Sunday, police said there had been an altercation between two groups of people at the velodrome carpark. A scene examination has been carried out as well as a post-mortem.\u00a0", "\"Our thoughts and sympathies are with Mr Tauiti's family who Police, alongside Victim Support, have been supporting at this tragic time,\" police said on Monday.", "\"His family have requested privacy while they are grieving and do not wish to be contacted by media.", "\"Counties Manukau Police are making good progress as the homicide investigation into Mr Tauiti's death continues.", "\"A number of individuals have been spoken to by the investigation team and Police will continue to identify and speak with people in connection to this incident.", "\"Anyone with information regarding the incident at the velodrome carpark between the hours of 5am and 6am on Saturday January 1st is asked to contact Police on 105, quoting file number 220101/8975 or you can provide information anonymously by ringing Crime Stoppers on 0800 555 111.\""]
